<TR><TD bgcolor="#bfbf80" colspan="3"><FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" SIZE="+1" color="4a0000"><a name="skills"></a><B>Bard Skills</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD bgcolor="#cdcd9c" colspan="3">
<FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" size="-1">
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>1H Slashing (Level 1)</B><BR>
The use of 1H Slashing weapons. (axes, swords)<BR><BR>
<B>1H Blunt  (Level 1)</B><BR>
The use of 1H Blunt weapons. (maces, hammers, clubs)<BR><BR>
<B>Bind Wound (Level 1)</B><BR>
Ability to bandage up your wounds if you have bandages.<BR><BR>
<B>Hand to Hand (Level 1)</B><BR>
Determines your attacking skill with no weapons equipped.
Some bards use instruments during battle to increase their song effects, so
a high hand-to-hand skill will still allow you to get some punches in while
you're strumming away.<BR><BR>
<B>Piercing (Level 1)</B><BR>
The use of piercing weapons.  (daggers, spears, rapiers)<BR><BR>
<B>Singing (Level 1)</B><BR>
When ever you aren't using the correct instrument for a song this skill is what your success is based
on. Some songs also require no instrument for full effects.<BR><BR>
<B>Throwing (Level 1)</B><BR>
The use of throwing weapons.<BR><BR>
<B>Percussion (Level 5)</B><BR>
This skill will allow you to equip a drum and increase the effects of any song which uses the percussion skill. Used
for many buffing and speed related songs.<BR><BR>
<B>String (Level 8)</B><BR>
This skill allows you to equip a string instrument such as a lute, which increases the effects of songs based on
string instruments. Used for healing and lulling type songs.<BR><BR>
<B>Dodge (Level 10)</B><BR>
This allows you to avoid damage by dodging the
incoming attacks.<BR><BR>
<B>Brass (Level 11)</B><BR>
Allows you to increase the effects of brass
songs by equipping a horn of some sort. Used for many offensive songs.<BR><BR>
<B>Forage (Level 12)</B><BR>
Unless you are a elf, then it's an innate
skill. Allows you to forage food and water from the land.<BR><BR>
<B>Wind (Level 14)</B><BR>
Allows you to increase the effects of wind based songs by equipping a wind instrument such as a flute. Used for many utility
songs such as invisability and ultravision, as well as some will bending songs such as charm and faction raising.<BR><BR>
<B>Dual Wield (Level 17)</B><BR>
This allows you to wield two seperate one handed weapons at once. The higher your skill, the more often you will
attack with your off hand.<BR><BR>
<B>Sneak (Level 17)</B><BR>
Allows you to sneak past mobs as long as they can't see you.<BR><BR>
<B>Safe Fall (Level 24)</B><BR>
Allows you to fall further and take less damage. A very useful skill for a bard since your speed song will normally cause
damage when you race over sand dunes and other hilly terrain.<BR><BR>
<B>Hide (Level 25)</B><BR>
You can hide while not moving and avoid being attacked. Not
always successful and there is no real way to tell if you are hidden or not. Elves get this skill at level 1.<BR><BR>
<B>Instill Doubt (Level 26)</B><BR>
This skill is shared with the monk and rogue class. When fighting a mob, you can use this skill to fear the mob and
make them run away. Also allows you to wave your weapons around menacingly while not fighting.<BR><BR>
<B>Disarm Traps (Level 30)</B><BR>
Not the most useful skill, the traps in the game are
not well implemented. Things may be different in the lands of Kunark. (editor's note: fat chance!)<BR><BR>
<B>Track (Level 35)</B><BR>
A very useful skill for finding out what mobs are in your
vicinity. Allows you to keep tabs on any rare mobs that may appear near you.<BR><BR>
<B>Pick Locks (Level 40)</B><BR>
Allows you to open locked doors without having a key.<BR><BR>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</font>
